First Read: 10-Feb-26
SB272 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to public records requests; to require
5 redaction from requested public records information that could
6 be used to initiate a financial transaction; to prohibit the
7 use of public records requested from a local board of
8 education, which contain lists of names and addresses of
9 individuals or entities, for the purpose of soliciting those
10 individuals or entities; to authorize the Attorney General to
11 impose civil penalties for violations; and to authorize the
12 State Board of Education to adopt rules.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. When any records relating to a public
15 contract for goods or services are requested pursuant to
16 Article 3 of Chapter 12 of Title 36, Code of Alabama 1975, the
17 public officer having custody of the records shall redact
18 account numbers, tax identification numbers, routing numbers,
19 employee identification numbers, sensitive personally
20 identifying information as defined in Section 8-38-2, Code of
21 Alabama 1975, and similar information that may be used to
22 initiate a financial transaction.
23 Section 2. (a) No person shall knowingly sell, give, or
24 receive any list of names and addresses contained in or
25 derived from public records requested from a local board of
26 education for the purpose of selling or offering for sale any
27 property or service to those individuals or entities listed
28 therein.
Page 1

therein.
SB272 Enrolled
29 (b) Any person subject to this section who knowingly
30 violates subsection (a) shall be liable for the payment of a
31 civil penalty in an action brought by the Attorney General not
32 to exceed five hundred dollars ($500) for each violation.
33 (c) If a request is made for public records that
34 contain the names or addresses of individuals or entities
35 which the public officer having custody of the records has
36 reasonable cause to believe may be used in violation of
37 subsection (a), prior to responding to the request, the public
38 officer may require the person requesting the records or
39 information therein to provide, in addition to the
40 certification described in Section 36-12-45(b)(3), Code of
41 Alabama 1975, a written certification that the requester does
42 not intend to, and will not:
43 (1) Use any list of names or addresses contained in or
44 derived from the records or information for the purpose of
45 selling or offering for sale any property or service to any
46 individual or entity listed or to any individual who resides
47 at any address listed; or
48 (2) Sell, give, or otherwise make available to any
49 person any list of names or addresses contained in or derived
50 from the records or information for the purpose of allowing
51 that person to sell or offer for sale any property or service
52 to any individual or entity listed or to any individual who
53 resides at any address listed.
54 (d) This section shall not impose any liability on a
55 public officer having custody of a record for granting access
56 to or providing copies of public records or information
Page 2

to or providing copies of public records or information
SB272 Enrolled
57 containing names and addresses, in good faith compliance with
58 subsection (c), to a person who has made a written request for
59 access to such information and has executed a written
60 certification pursuant to subsection (c).
61 (e) The State Board of Education, by rule, may provide
62 guidance and a model certification form for custodians of
63 public records to implement this section.
64 Section 3. This act shall become effective immediately.
